# Agentboard Session Rules

At the start of every session:

1. Read `.platform/work/BRIEF.md` to load the current sprint brief and active context.
2. Read `.platform/work/ACTIVE.md` to see what stream is in flight and its current stage.
3. If `.platform/` does not exist, this project is not yet activated — suggest running `agentboard init` then activating.

## Workflow

Follow the 6-stage protocol defined in `.platform/workflow.md`:
triage → research → propose → execute → verify → log

Never self-declare a stream complete. Present evidence and let the developer close it.

## Context files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `.platform/work/BRIEF.md` | Current sprint scope and priorities |
| `.platform/work/ACTIVE.md` | Active stream, stage, and next action |
| `.platform/STATUS.md` | Feature status and roadmap |
| `.platform/architecture.md` | System design and invariants |
| `.platform/memory/decisions.md` | Locked decisions — read before proposing changes |
| `.platform/memory/log.md` | Session history |
